result.execSummary:
The defendant Skipper D. Johnson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Failure to Support Child (<120 Days), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(3).
  • Failure to Support Child (<120 Days), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(3).
  • Failure to Support Child (<120 Days), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(3).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
DA Gerald Fox appeared for the State.  Defendant appeared in person and with Attorney Poss.  Plead no contest to amended Counts 1, 2 and 3.  Misd. Failure to support.  Counts 4 and 5 dismissed, but read in for sentencing purposes.  Motion to amend granted.  Court recited the charge and possible penalties on the counts he plead to.  Defendant understood.  Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant.  Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the plea.   Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily, and intelligently entered his pleas and waived his constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Found guilty of Misd. Failure to Support Child, contrary to 948.22(3).  State recommended:  probation, 2 years.  Concurrent.  DNA sample.  Strictly comply the child support orders, and as amended from time to time.  Maintain bi-weekly contact with his child support worker.  s/m employment.  Not to terminate without prior agent approval.  

Court ordered:  sentence withheld, 2 years probation.  Concurrent.  Strictly comply with his child support orders, as amended from time to time.  Comply with all rules of child support.  Maintain  contact with his child support worker a minimum of 2 times per month, unless directed otherwise by his agent.  Obtain and maintain employment.  Not to terminate without prior agent approval.    The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by a risk and needs assessment and the probation agent.  Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions. DNA sample.  CC.
DA Gerald Fox appeared for the State.  Defendant appeared through Attorney Fredrickson.  Plea/sentencing has been set for 7/11 at 1:30 pm.
